external_knowledge:
- 'More than one shipped order for the same item and size' implies that the customer has ordered the same item in the same size multiple times, and all of these orders have been shipped; 
- Average rise measurement is calculated based on rise measurements in the rise_measurements table;
- Length type refers to a specific measurement value (e.g., 30", 32", 34") that corresponds to the size of the clothing item.

- In this context, 'flexible fashion items' refers to clothing items that support custom size charts; 
- 'flexibility' is a metaphor for customizability in size; 
- 'exceeds 80 units' means the average length measurement is greater than 80.
